https://github.com/libp2p/rust-libp2p/issues/1890 reports `libp2p-pnet` to use an outdated dependency. More specifically `salsa20` `v0.6.0` instead of `v0.7.0`. With https://github.com/libp2p/rust-libp2p/pull/1744 Dependabot should detect these outdated dependencies and propose a pull request.

`libp2p-pnet` (as well as `libp2p-deflate`) was not part of the `workspace` list in the root `Cargo.toml`. By adding `libp2p-pnet` (as well as `libp2p-deflate`) to the list Dependabot should now check `libp2p-pnet` as well.

